{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01VhdS6NopHEPDYEf2o5Gw22","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The cluster is currently on v24.1.0 and I need to upgrade it to v24.1.1. All 3 nodes are healthy and available. \n\nThe plan for a controlled rolling update:\n1. Set a partition on the StatefulSet to control the rollout (start with partition=3 to prevent any automatic updates)\n2. Update the image to v24.1.1\n3. Roll out one node at a time by decreasing the partition value\n4. Wait for each pod to become Ready before proceeding to the next\n\nLet me do this step by step:\n\n1. First set partition=3 (prevents any pod from being updated yet)\n2. Update the image to v24.1.1\n3. Then lower the partition incrementally from 3 down to 0, updating one pod at a time and waiting for each to be ready before moving to the next\n\nCockroachDB best practice is to update from the highest index down to maintain quorum during the rolling update.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":615,"cache_read_input_tokens":29185,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":615},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f67d4b76-a931-4ac1-8ea8-5da27f00b60d","uuid":"fb3322fb-10fc-4986-ae48-ee1b0c28de0a","request_id":"req_011Ccenh7X7xtTi1LfeL5CrT"}
